question: Rohtang Tunnel is renamed after which Prime Minister?
explanation: Rohtand Tunnel is renamed after former Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee as the Atal Tunnel. It is the highway tunnel built under the Rohtang Pass in the eastern Pir Panjal range of the Himalayas on the Leh-Manali Highway and is the world's longest highway tunnel above 10000 feet.
